# Custom Embedded Linux with Buildroot

A minimal custom Linux image built from scratch using Buildroot, targeting ARM architecture and booted on QEMU emulator. Includes a custom init script, SSH access via Dropbear, and a fully assembled root filesystem.

---

## What This Project Does

- Builds a complete Linux system from source using Buildroot
- Cross-compiles everything for ARM (armv7l) on an x86-64 host machine
- Boots the image on a QEMU ARM VExpress emulator
- Runs a custom init script at boot
- Exposes SSH access via Dropbear

---

## System Overview

| Component | Details |
|----------|---------|
| Build system | Buildroot 2024.02 |
| Target architecture | ARM (armv7l) |
| Board | QEMU VExpress-A9 |
| Kernel | Linux 6.1.44 |
| Init system | BusyBox init |
| SSH server | Dropbear |
| Host machine | Ubuntu 22.04 (x86-64) |

...


